  "title": "Unit Testing Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "Learn how to write effective unit tests for cron-driven tasks integrated with FastAPI using Python 3.12+. This explainer demonstrates best practices and a sample project structure.",

  "key_points": [
    "Understand the importance of testing cron-driven tasks",
    "Create a test suite within your FastAPI application",
    "Mock the required dependencies like schedulers or external APIs",
    "Write test cases for individual functions in the cron tasks",
    "Use Pytest, a popular Python testing framework",
    "Leverage Python 3.12+ features like async/await and type hints for cleaner tests"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock\n# Your cron task function\ndef my_cron_task(scheduler):\n    pass\n\napp = FastAPI()\nmy_mock_scheduler = Mock(spec=...)\nmy_app = FastAPI()\n\n@my_app.on_event('test_my_cron_task')\ndef test_my_cron_task():\n    my_mock_scheduler.run_job.assert_called_once()\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for async/await syntax and improved type hints",
    "FastAPI 0.69.0 or higher is recommended due to improvements in test functionality"
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Mocking dependencies like schedulers can be tricky, ensure your mock has the same interface as the original dependency",
    "Remember that unit tests should not test external dependencies; focus on testing your cron task function's logic instead"
  ]
